<H1>Joseph F. Traub</H1>
<!WA0><IMG ALIGN=right SRC="http://www.cs.columbia.edu/~traub/traub.gif" WIDTH=141 HEIGHT=169 ALT="">
<P>
I am a Professor of Computer Science in the
<!WA1><A HREF="http://www.cs.columbia.edu/">
Columbia University Computer Science Department</A>.
<P>
Much of my research is joint work with Professor 
<!WA2><A HREF="http://www.cs.columbia.edu/~henryk/">
Henryk Wozniakowski</A>.
The work ranges from fundamental research on information-based
complexity to large-scale applications in mathematical finance to the
building of software.  I'll discuss some aspects of this work.
<P>
<HR>
<UL> 
<LI> <!WA3><A HREF="http://www.cs.columbia.edu/~traub/ibc.html"> Information-Based Complexity</A>
<LI> <!WA4><A HREF="http://www.cs.columbia.edu/~traub/intract.html"> Breaking Intractability</A>
<LI> <!WA5><A HREF="http://www.cs.columbia.edu/~traub/finance.html"> Financial Computations</A>
<LI> <!WA6><A HREF="http://www.cs.columbia.edu/~traub/discrep.html"> Low Discrepancy Algorithms</A>
<LI> <!WA7><A HREF="http://www.cs.columbia.edu/~traub/path.html"> Path Integrals</A>
<LI> <!WA8><A HREF="http://www.cs.columbia.edu/~traub/random.html"> Randomization</A>
<LI> <!WA9><A HREF="http://www.cs.columbia.edu/~traub/scilim.html"> Limits to Scientific Knowledge</A>
</UL>
<HR>
<P>
You may look at my list of
<!WA10><A HREF="http://www.cs.columbia.edu/~traub/pubs.html">publications</A>,
some of which are available online.
